-- Kerry Starts Nine-Day Global Trip With Turkey Meetings
-- B y   F l a v i a   K r a u s e - J a c k s o n
-- 2013-04-04T23:34:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-04/kerry-starts-nine-day-global-trip-with-turkey-meetings.html
U.S. Secretary of State  John Kerry 
will travel April 6 to Istanbul to meet with Turkish officials
on Syria and other issues, the State Department announced.  Turkey is the first stop on a nine-day trip, followed by
travel to Jerusalem on April 7 to begin a three-day Middle East
stop that includes meetings with Israeli and Palestinian
Authority leaders, State Department spokeswoman Victoria Nuland
said in a statement released today.  After a meeting with the Group of Eight foreign ministers
in London on April 10-11, Kerry is to travel to Seoul on April
12, Beijing on April 13 and Tokyo on April 14. The top U.S.
diplomat is scheduled to return to Washington from Japan on
April 15.  To contact the reporter on this story:
